In England, in the seven days to 28 January, there were 612,191 new confirmed cases (1,082.6 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 21 January, there were 633,497 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 3% (21,306 fewer cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 02 February is 15,028,951 (26,576.3 cases per 100,000 population).
